{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2014}} {{Use British English|date=January 2014}} {{infobox music festival | | music_festival_name = Camp Bestival | image = Camp Bestival, 2014 Logo.jpg | caption=Camp Bestival, 2014 Logo | location = [[Dorset]], [[England]] | years_active= 2008 - present | dates = Summer - July, August (4 days) | genre = [[Indie music|Indie]]/[[Dance music|Dance]] | website = [http://www.campbestival.net/ www.campbestival.net] }}
'''Camp Bestival''' is a British [[music festival]], the "little sister" of [[Bestival]], both organised by BBC Radio 1 DJ [[Rob Da Bank]]. It is held annually, in July, at [[Lulworth Castle]] in Dorset<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dorsetecho.co.uk/news/4498422.Lulworth_Castle_all_set_for_Camp_Bestival/|title=Lulworth Castle all set for Camp Bestival|last=Meech|first=Ruth|date=17 July 2009|work=Dorset Echo|accessdate=2009-07-28}}</ref> and is targeted at families with small children.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/dorset/content/articles/2007/11/05/bestival_2008_feature.shtml|title=Camp Bestival 2009|work=BBC Dorset|accessdate=2009-07-28}}</ref> It has a capacity of 30,000.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dorsetecho.co.uk/news/4513321.Camp_Bestival_is_a_real_family_affair/|title=Camp Bestival is a real family affair|last=Hendy|first=Arron|author2=Miriam Phillips|date=27 July 2009|work=Dorset Echo|accessdate=2009-07-28}}</ref> It won the Best New Festival award from the [[UK Festival Awards]] in 2008<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.festivalawards.com/index.cfm?section=awards.nominees&method=view&year=2008&eventid=1228|title=Camp Bestival 2008|year=2008|work=UK Festival Awards|accessdate=2009-07-28}}</ref> and Best Family Festival in 2009, 2010, 2013 and 2014.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.billboard.biz/bbbiz/content_display/industry/e3id27113ae043af5fc3e60be32ed5ed5f7|title=PJ Harvey Confirmed For Camp Bestival|last=Wilson|first=Jen|date=6 February 2009 |work=Billboard.biz|accessdate=2009-07-28}}</ref>
==2008== [[File:Camp Bestival 2008 at night.jpg|right|thumb|2008 Camp Bestival at night]] The first Camp Bestival in 2008 included headliners [[Chuck Berry]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nme.com/news/chuckberry/38284|title=Chuck Berry dazzles first day of Camp Bestival|date=19 July 2008|work=NME|accessdate=2009-07-28}}</ref> [[Flaming Lips]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nme.com/news/flaming-lips/38336|title=Flaming Lips: 'Camp Bestival best festival we've played'|date=22 July 2008|work=NME|accessdate=2009-07-28}}</ref> [[Kate Nash]], Billy Bragg, DJ Yoda, Kevin Rowland, Eliza Doolittle and Black Kids,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/england/dorset/7516020.stm|title=Castle hosts family Camp Bestival|date=20 July 2008|work=BBC News|accessdate=2009-07-28}}</ref> but was troubled by the overcrowding of the campsites leading to many people camping by their cars in the nearby carparks.{{Citation needed|date=July 2009}}
==2009== The 2009 festival, held over the weekend 24–26 July, included musical performances by [[Florence and the Machine]], [[PJ Harvey]] - in her only UK solo appearance of the year,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nme.com/news/pj-harvey/46349|title=PJ Harvey debuts new songs at Camp Bestival|date=28 July 2009|work=NME|accessdate=2009-07-28}}</ref>Chic, [[Will Young]], [[Tinchy Stryder]], [[VV Brown]], Kid Creole and the Coconuts,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/england/dorset/8168760.stm|title=Castle hosts family Camp Bestival |date=25 July 2009|work=BBC News|accessdate=2009-07-28}}</ref> Mercury Rev, Goldie Lookin' Chain, Wild Beasts, Roots Manuva, Candi Staton, Bon Iver, Phoenix, Alessi's Ark, Alela Diane, Micachu and the Shapes, Golden Silvers, Seth Lakeman and Laura Marling. Comedians appearing included [[Frankie Boyle]], [[Marcus Brigstocke]], [[Lee Mack]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/features/bestival-this-years-festivals-boast-an-array-of-nonmusical-delights-1757388.html|title=Bestival: This year's festivals boast an array of non-musical delights|last=Sharp|first=Rob|date=23 July 2009|work=The Independent|accessdate=2009-07-28}}</ref> and [[Michael "Atters" Attree]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.campbestival.net/html/magicmeadow/timeforteasepresentstofflins |title=Camp Bestival 2014 |publisher=Camp Bestival |accessdate=2014-06-08}}</ref> Other events included a barn dance, a show by the [[English National Ballet]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bournemouthecho.co.uk/news/4513058.Camp_Bestival_hailed_great_success___updated/|title=Camp Bestival hailed great success|last=Morton|first=James|date=27 July 2009|work=Bournemouth Echo|accessdate=2009-07-28}}</ref> and [[Hugh Fearnley-Whittingstall]]'s River Cottage tent.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dorsetecho.co.uk/news/4512146.Thousands_at_Camp_Bestival/|title=Thousands at Camp Bestival|last=Hendy|first=Arron|date=25 July 2009|work=Dorset Echo|accessdate=2009-07-28}}</ref>
Changes from the previous year included a late-night Silent Disco to avoid waking children, and the number of toilets were tripled.<ref name="lite">{{cite news|url=http://www.thisislondon.co.uk/music/gig-23414865-details/Camp+Bestival/gigReview.do?reviewId=23724522|title=Camp Bestival is big on charm|last=de Lacey|first=Martha|date=27 July 2009 |work=London Lite|accessdate=2009-07-28}}</ref>
==2010== The line-up for Camp Bestival 2010 included [[Madness (band)|Madness]], [[Calvin Harris]], [[Billy Bragg]], [[The Human League]], [[Lee "Scratch" Perry]] and [[The Cuban Brothers]]. The festival was held over the weekend of 30 July to 1 August.
==2011== The 2011 Festival has now been extended to allow campers to arrive from the Thursday lunchtime, after complaints about the long time needed to get on site caused some festival-goers to miss some of the Friday attractions in 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.campbestival.net/tickets/thursday-camping-tickets |title=Tickets |publisher=Camp Bestival |accessdate=2014-06-08}}</ref>
Headliners for 2011 are confirmed as [[Blondie (band)|Blondie]], [[Mark Ronson|Mark Ronson and the Business International]] and [[Primal Scream]] who will be performing the [[Screamadelica]] album in its entirety in celebration of its 20-year anniversary. Other performers include [[ABC (band)|ABC]], [[The Wonder Stuff]], [[House of Pain]], [[Eliza Doolittle (singer)|Eliza Doolittle]], [[Bad Shepherds]], [[Easy Star All-Stars]] and [[Ed Sheeran]]. {{citation needed|date=August 2014}}
Comedy performers include [[Marcus Brigstock]], [[Milton Jones]], [[Marcus Walsh]] and [[Jack Whitehall]] whilst there will be spoken word from [[Laura Dockrell]], [[Simon Day]] and [[Sam Leith]] plus a continuation of the popular "How to..." series with speakers including [[Howard Marks]]. {{citation needed|date=August 2014}}
Family entertainment included [[Mr Tumble]], live performances of The [[Gruffalo]] and [[Shrek: The Musical]] and "100 Free things for Kids". {{citation needed|date=August 2014}}
==2012== 2012 Camp Bestival had an Olympic theme following the [[London 2012]] Olympic games. The 2012 headliners included [[Kool and the Gang]], [[Chic (band)|Chic]] featuring [[Nile Rodgers]], [[Hot Chip]], [[The Happy Mondays]], [[Rizzle Kicks]], [[Stooshe]] and [[Rolf Harris]]. Other entertainment included [[Jimmy Carr]], [[Mr Tumble]] and [[Russel Kane]] plus entertainment from The Gruffalo Live, and Shrek the Musical.
==2013== The 2013 Festival was held over the first four days in August and themed 'around the world'. This year featured the addition of the dance space and science tent but the removal of the 'Little Big Top'.
Headliners included [[Richard Hawley]], [[Levellers (band)|Levellers]] and [[Labrinth]], Other performers included [[DJ Fresh]], [[The Farm (British band)|The Farm]], [[Kid Creole and the Coconuts]], [[Mark Owen]] and [[Gabrielle Aplin]]. This year also featured a world record attempt for the most paper aeroplanes flying at once in support of the new [[Disney]]/[[Pixar]] movie [[Planes (film)|Planes]].
Other performers included [[London Grammar]], [[JAWS (band)|JAWS]], [[The 1975]] and [[Clean Bandit]].
==2014==
Camp Bestival 2014 ran from July 31 - August 3 and had the theme of "Circus". The festivals 2014 headliners were [[Basement Jaxx]], [[De La Soul]] and [[James (band)|James]].
Other acts and artists appearing across the weekend included [[Johnny Marr]], [[Sinéad O'Connor]], [[Pop Will Eat Itself]], [[Laura Mvula]], [[Steve Mason (musician)|Steve Mason]], [[The Skatalites]], [[Peter Hook & The Light]], [[The Cuban Brothers]], [[MNEK]], [[Wilkinson (musician)|Wilkinson]], [[Chas & Dave]], [[Sophie Ellis-Bextor]] and [[Nick Mulvey]].
==The event== Camp bestival features a variety of activities and entertainment throughout the festival. Apart from a 4-days long line-up, the festival offers comedy shows, literature programmes, a kids area, workshops and performances.
Food stall and tents are available all over the festival site.
