{{Infobox restaurant | name = The Cat & Fiddle | logo = | logo_width = | logo_alt = | image = | image_width = | image_alt = | image_caption = | pushpin_map = | map_width = | map_alt = | map_caption = | slogan = | established = 1982<!-- {{Start date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | closed = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | current-owner = | previous-owner = [[Kim Gardner]] | chef = | head-chef = | food-type = [[British cuisine]] | dress-code = | rating = | street-address = 742 N [[Highland Avenue (Los Angeles)|Highland Avenue]] | city = [[Hollywood]] | county = [[Los Angeles County]] | state = [[California]] | postcode = | country = [[United States]] | coordinates = {{coord|34.097687|-118.332646|type:landmark_globe:earth_region:US-CA}} | seating-capacity = | reservations = | other-locations = | other-information = | website = {{URL|thecatandfiddle.com}} }}
'''''The Cat & Fiddle''''' is British Pub<ref name=LT/> and restaurant located in Hollywood, California.<ref name=LAT>[http://touch.latimes.com/#section/-1/article/p2p-81730228/ Los Angeles Times]</ref><ref>[http://www.kcet.org/socal/departures/columns/lost-landmarks/building-a-family-past-present-and-future-of-the-cat-fiddle-pub.html KCET]</ref><ref>[http://losangeles.cbslocal.com/2014/10/20/hollywood-gem-cat-and-fiddle-may-close-doors-for-chain-restaurant/ CBS]</ref>
The Pub was originally opened in Laurel Canyon by British musician [[Kim Gardner]] in 1982 <ref name=LAT/>. The establishment moved to [[Sunset Boulevard]] in 1985<ref name=LAT/> where it remained for nearly 30 years. In 2017 The Cat & Fiddle moved to its current location at 742 North Highland Avenue<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thecatandfiddle.com|title=Welcome|website=The Cat and Fiddle Restaurant & Pub|language=en-US|access-date=2018-08-03}}</ref>. Celebrities such as [[Keith Moon]], [[Rod Stewart]], [[Robert Plant]],<ref name=LT>{{cite web|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|title=Kim Gardner, 53; British Pub Owner, Former Musician|date=October 31, 2001|first=Dennis|last=McLellan|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2001/oct/31/local/me-63864}}</ref> [[Christopher Lloyd]], [[Drew Barrymore]] and [[Morrissey]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.expressandstar.com/news/2013/08/03/noel-russell-morrissey-and-a-taste-of-the-black-country-in-hollywood/|title=Noel, Russell, Morrissey – and a taste of the Black Country in Hollywood|website=www.expressandstar.com|language=en|access-date=2018-08-03}}</ref> have been regulars over the years.<ref name=LAT/>
