{{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Musicians --> | name = The New Orleans Bingo! Show | image = | caption = | image_size = | background = group_or_band | alias = | origin = New Orleans | instrument = | genre = [[Rock music|rock]] | occupation = | years_active = | label = | associated_acts = [[Morning 40 Federation]], [[Preservation Hall Jazz Band]], [[Noisician Coalition]], [[Liquidrone]] | website = https://www.facebook.com/The.New.Orleans.Bingo.Show/ | current_members = Clint Maedgen, Ron Rona, Mattvaughan Black, Michael Miller, Lucas Davenport, Keith Hajjar, Trixie Minx | past_members = Earl Scioneaux III, Marty Lastrapes, VeVe LaRoux }} '''The New Orleans Bingo! Show''' is an interactive theatrical [[cabaret]] and musical band from [[New Orleans, Louisiana]].<ref name="gambit">[http://www.bestofneworleans.com/dispatch/2007-10-23/feat3.php Bingo! Parlour] Alison Fensterstock, ''Gambit Weekly'', October 23, 2007, Retrieved July 24, 2008</ref> The show features original music by New Orleans singer and songwriter Clint Maedgen who created the show in 2002.<ref>[http://blog.nola.com/chrisrose/2008/01/the_60second_interview_clint_m.html The 60-Second Interview: Clint Maedgen] Chris Rose, ''The Times-Picayune'', January 4, 2008, Retrieved July 24, 2008</ref> The show also features original short films, comedic skits and a live game of [[Bingo (U.S.)|bingo]] played with the audience. The group toured with the [[Preservation Hall Jazz Band]] in 2007 and 2008.<ref name="gambit" />
The Bingo! Show played at The [[Voodoo Experience]] held at City Park in New Orleans, Louisiana over Halloween weekend for several years.<ref>http://www.musicnewsnet.com/2009/06/new-orleans-voodoo-experience-fest-line-up-announced.html</ref> As of 2017, they last performed in 2014.<ref>[https://www.facebook.com/The.New.Orleans.Bingo.Show/ The New Orleans Bingo! Show Facebook Page] The New Orleans Bingo! Show Facebook Page, Retrieved July 8, 2017</ref>
